<span id="freeTextContainer6964812879768288087">Reread - April 2021. <br/><br/>Still a 5 star read, but mainly for nostalgic purposes. If I read it for the first time now, it might be a 4 star. It’s interesting to see how my thoughts towards the characters have changed. As an adult I relate a lot to both Elinor and Dustfinger, but find Meggie a bit annoying at times. <br/><br/>Still a truly magical tale that will always hold a special place in my heart.<br/><br/>*************************<br/><br/>Original read 2016. <br/><br/>Honestly one of my favourite fantasy reads. I loved all the charac</span>
  <span id="freeText6964812879768288087" style="display:none">Reread - April 2021. <br /><br />Still a 5 star read, but mainly for nostalgic purposes. If I read it for the first time now, it might be a 4 star. It’s interesting to see how my thoughts towards the characters have changed. As an adult I relate a lot to both Elinor and Dustfinger, but find Meggie a bit annoying at times. <br /><br />Still a truly magical tale that will always hold a special place in my heart.<br /><br />*************************<br /><br />Original read 2016. <br /><br />Honestly one of my favourite fantasy reads. I loved all the characters - even the villians! They were vivid, colourful, the world Cornelia Funke creates is absolutely extraordinary and if it were up to me I would live in the Inkworld for ever!<br />For anyone that likes a good dose of escapism, a book about books, a story that will make you laugh, cry and just generally never want to finish then this is for you!<br />5 stars!</span>
