<div id="review_52038999" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/52038999" />
    <a title="Anne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1720620-anne"><img alt="Anne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1415374035p2/1720620.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/52038999?book_show_action=true">Apr 09, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anne" href="/user/show/1720620-anne">Anne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1720620-anne?shelf=read-in-2009">read-in-2009</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1720620-anne?shelf=middle-grade-reader">middle-grade-reader</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1720620-anne?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer52038999" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7523682738257799133">I was a little disappointed. I think it was because it couldn&apos;t quite live up to the hype for me. It was still a pretty good read though.<br/>I&apos;m planning on reading the other two books in the series. Maybe they will be better.<br/>My biggest complaint would have to be that I don&apos;t think my kids would relate well to the heroine, Meggie. The story centers around a father and daughter who love books. I mean really looove books. I got a little sick of hearing about it, to be honest. Yes. Books are great. We </span>
  <span id="freeText7523682738257799133" style="display:none">I was a little disappointed. I think it was because it couldn't quite live up to the hype for me. It was still a pretty good read though.<br />I'm planning on reading the other two books in the series. Maybe they will be better.<br />My biggest complaint would have to be that I don't think my kids would relate well to the heroine, Meggie. The story centers around a father and daughter who love books. I mean really looove books. I got a little sick of hearing about it, to be honest. Yes. Books are great. We get it. At one point, Meggie recalls how her father lovingly strokes the cover of a book before he opens it. Huh? Even when Meggie is being held captive by the villain, she is looking for something to read. I thought it was a bit much. <br />Like I said, I'm still hoping the other two books will be better.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7523682738257799133" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


